AND Proxy for copper oxychloride: Stoechiometric calculation: Copper oxychloride: Cu(OH)3Cl: molecular mass: 213.57 g/mol, Cu: 63.55 g/mol, Cu: 59.51%. Calculated value: 100% of input quantity. Calculated based on 2009 pesticide application values from Dabrowski, Shadung, & Wepener (2014) and König (2015) with data on production area from FAO (2012). 
Further references: Dabrowski, J. M., Shadung, J. M., & Wepener, V. (2014). Prioritizing agricultural pesticides used in South Africa based on their environmental mobility and potential human health effects. Environment international, 62, 31-40; Koenig, A. (2015). Environmental hotspots and the potential of clean technologies in the South African fruit supply chain. Master thesis at Zurich University of applied Sciences (ZHAW), Institute of Natural Resource Sciences, unpublished; FAO. (2012). Citrus Fruit - Fresh and proceeded - Annual Statistics.

